<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Liverpool owner John Henry celebrated his 71st birthday in style over the weekend with a specially-themed cake.</p>

<p>Henry, who took over at Anfield 10 years ago, enjoyed a birthday to remember after also seeing the reigning champions run out 4-3 winners in a thrilling season-opener against Leeds.</p>

<p>And the 71-year-old American was treated to a special birthday cake over the weekend, featuring all the trophies won by Liverpool over the last year-and-a-half.</p>

<p>Liverpool owner John Henry celebrated his birthday in style with this specially-themed cake</p>

<p>The cake consisted of the Champions League, Premier League, the FIFA Club World Cup and the UEFA Super Cup.</p>

<p>Henry, who recently revealed his pride after Liverpool won their first ever Premier League title, saw Liverpool edge out newly-promoted Leeds in a rollercoaster of a game at Anfield on Saturday.</p>

<p>Jurgen Klopp's side were pegged back three times by Marcelo Bielsa's outfit but the champions yet again found a way to win.</p>

<p>The Reds clinched their first-ever Premier League title last season after an emphatic campaign</p>

<p>Prior to their title triumph, Liverpool clinched the Champions League the season before</p>

<p>Mohamed Salah struck an 88th minute winner from the penalty spot to seal his hat-trick after Virgil van Dijk had also scored for the Reds.</p>

<p>Klopp will be demanding much more from his squad during their next Premier League outing when they meet Chelsea on Sunday at Stamford Bridge.</p>

<p>The Blues are threatening a title pursuit of their own after a lavish spree in the summer transfer window, spending £230million on Kai Havertz, Timo Werner, Ben Chilwell and Hakim Ziyech while also acquiring Thiago Silva and Malang Sarr for free. </p>

<p>Liverpool started their season with a thrilling 4-3 victory over Leeds on Saturday at Anfield</p>
